verbose_text: Evolution of Thromboelastogram After Timber Rattlesnake Envenomation Rachael C Westover, Andrew F Micciche, Shirley Shao, Alexander M Sidlak, Anthony F Pizon University of Pittsburgh, Pittsburgh, PA, USA Background : Serial platelet and fibrinogen levels are often obtained after crotalid envenomation to determine level of coagulopathy.
